Let T degree celsius be the required temperature. Let V 1and V 2 be the velocity of sound at temperatures
T 1 Kelvin and T 2 kelvin respectively. T 1 = 273 Kelvin (0 degree celsius) and T 2 = (T degree Celsius + 273) Kelvin
V 2 by V 1 = square root of T 2 by T 1 = square root of 273 + T / square root of 273 = 2
Here it is given that V 2 by V 1 = 2
So, 273 + T / 273 = 4
T = (273 × 4) - 273 = 819degree Celsius.

